      <div class="tab-pane fade" id="constructs">
        <div class="lead text-info">Constructs</div>
        <p>
          Constructs are compiled thoughts that have been created with much deliberation and thought. It is an essay which depicts a
          concept of yours in a detailed manner.<br><br>

          Function of Each Tab under Constructs Tab in Thinker Panel-<br>
          <strong class="text-info">New Construct -</strong> The editor exists in New Construct Tab. You may use this editor extensively for your purpose
          or may write your Construct elsewhere and copy it here. Many options are present here eg - "Select Dossier", "Affinity Level", "Exhibit" etc ...<br>
          &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;Select Dossier - Directly insert the new construct into an already existing Dossier.<br>
          &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;Affinity Level - How much do you like the written Construct. Easier later on to define and categorize constructs.<br>
          &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;Exhibit Construct - This will directly exhibit the construct on creation. This cannot be undone. So please be sure of your construct.<br>
          <strong class="text-info">Organizer -</strong> We encourage extensive use of Dossiers. Organize your Constructs in Dossiers for easy recollection and second tier
          categorization. You can move any number of Constructs to a Dossier. You can have any number of Dossiers. You can easily remove constructs and add them to other Dossiers.<br>
          &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;StandAlone - Contains all the constructs not attached to any Dossier.<br>
          &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;Other Tabs below StandAlone are your dossiers containing your constructs.<br>
          &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;You can set the dossier quality according to your preference of the Dossier and its contents.
          <br>
          <strong class="text-info">List Constructs -</strong> Will list all your Constructs written till date. It has an option of displaying Constructs
          in any order you wish. Select the Choice from the Drop Down and "Display". Your required Constructs will be displayed. Each Block displays
          details about the construct, ie. Construct Quality, Dossier it belongs to, BrainStorms attached. It has easy options to immediately start reviewing or editing
          your constructs
          <br>
          <br>
          <strong class="text-info">BrainStorm Mapping -</strong>BrainStorm Sessions can be mapped to Constructs. To map a BrainStorm, start the
          Brain Storm Session you would like to map and click "Construct Mapping". Choose your construct and Map. One Construct can be mapped with only one
          BrainStorm. An already mapped BrainStorm cannot be mapped to another construct and vice versa.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tab-pane fade" id="cognitions">
        <div class="lead text-info">Cognitions</div>
        <p>
          Cognition is the mental action or process of acquiring knowledge and understanding through thought, experience, and deliberation. Cognitions are acquired through perception, sensation or intuition. These realizations generally result in the most innovative, intriguing and fascinating thoughts.
          Cognition is any form of cognitive activity. MentalConstructs has narrowed down "Cognitions" into 3 major subcategories. Epiphanies, BrainWaves and Factoids.<br>
          &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;Epiphanies - are a sudden manifestation of the essence or meaning of something or a comprehension or perception of reality by means of a sudden intuitive realization. Philosophical thoughts defining your own individual being.<br>
          &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;BrainWaves - are sudden ideas which may or may not be of monetary value but are inherent to your nature and you would like to build upon them.<br>
          &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;Factoids - are solid facts pertaining to any subject in general.<br><br>
          Under Cognitions Tab in the Thinker panel you will find -<br>
          <strong class="text-info">Median - Cogntions -</strong> It is a simple explanation of Cognitions and what it entails. Also it contains
          a few subcategory cognitions which display the most recent or most prized cognition<br>
          <strong class="text-info">Epiphanies -</strong> Contains all your recorded epiphanies in descending order of created at time.<br>
          <strong class="text-info">BrainWaves -</strong> Contains all your recorded brainwaves in descending order of affinity for the brain wave.<br>
          <strong class="text-info">Factoids -</strong> Contains all your recorded factoids in descending order of created at time.<br>
        </p>
      </div>

