      <div class="tab-pane fade" id="brain_storm">
        <div class="lead text-info">Brain Storms</div>
        <p>
          BrainStorms are sessions of increased mental acuity when thoughts flow faster than you can record them. It is when you think upon an idea and
          conceptualize it by categorizing them into relevant points. BrainStorm is an interactive tool which allows you to do so. Brain Storms should generally
          have one relevant Construct to which it should be mapped. The BrainStorm should be graphical representation of the Construct defined. <br><br>
          Function of Each Tab under BrainStorm Tab in Thinker Panel-<br>
          <strong class="text-info">List BrainStorms</strong> - Is a list of all the brain storms ever initiated. It hold general information like
          the Parent point of the BrainStorm, Construct it belongs to and options to review brain storms mapped to constructs. BrainStorm should not be left
          floating. It should be mapped to a Construct.<br>
          <strong class="text-info">BrainStorm Sessions</strong> - Will open up and show you the last BrainStorm you were working upon. To change the brainstorm click on "Start Different Session"
          button, either start a new brain storm session or select a previous one.<br>
          Under "Start" you would see data in two columns. The left is the parent point or main point and the right column holds the sub points or child points which
          belong to the respective parent point. Add data directly into them and keep building your brain storm. To map to a construct select "Construct Mapping" button
          and select construct to map with. One brain storm can belong to only on Construct.
          <br>
          This is the only place where editing of brain storms are allowed. BrainStorms are never finalized, they are always in editing mode. To view a complete
          brain storm, review the construct to which it is mapped.
        </p>
